      "claim": "We may assume B=(0,0), C=(1,0), A=(u,v) with v != 0, and W=(s,0).",
      "reasoning": "A similarity transformation preserves collinearity, perpendicularity, circles, orthocenters, and antipodal points on a circle. Since W lies on line BC, after translating, rotating, and scaling we may put BC on the x-axis with B=(0,0) and C=(1,0).",
