      "claim": "The orthocenter is H=(u, u(1-u)/v).",
      "reasoning": "Since BC is horizontal, the altitude from A is the vertical line x=u. The slope of AC is v/(u-1), so the altitude from B has slope -(u-1)/v=(1-u)/v and equation y=((1-u)/v)x. Substituting x=u gives H=(u,u(1-u)/v).",
      "facts_used": [
        "definition of orthocenter",
        "perpendicular slopes",
        "step 1"
