    },
    {
      "claim": "The point N is N=(u^2/(u^2+v^2), uv/(u^2+v^2)).",
      "reasoning": "The point N lies on AB and on HC. Since HC is an altitude, HC is perpendicular to AB, so N is the foot of the perpendicular from C to line AB. The projection of C=(1,0) onto the line through the origin in direction A=(u,v) is ((C dot A)/(A dot A))A = (u/(u^2+v^2))(u,v).",
      "facts_used": [
        "definition of altitude",
        "orthogonal projection formula",
