      "claim": "The point M is M=(v^2/((1-u)^2+v^2), v(1-u)/((1-u)^2+v^2)).",
      "reasoning": "The point M lies on AC and on HB. Since HB is an altitude, HB is perpendicular to AC, so M is the foot of the perpendicular from B to line AC. Writing AC with base C=(1,0) and direction A-C=(u-1,v), the projection parameter of B-C=(-1,0) onto A-C is (1-u)/((1-u)^2+v^2), giving the stated coordinates.",
